						<summary>

						<p>Slab near a wall called Polimēra-bhāvi to the east of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1665, Rudhirōdgāri, Vaiśākha śu. 7, Monday,</hi> corresponding to 1743 A.D. April 19.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to refer the boundary dispute between two villages Gūḍeṁ cheṟuvu and some other village (name lost).</p>						

						</summary>
